						<summary>

						<p>Slab in a field called Vishṇumūrti oḷa-māḍu.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Vira Sōyidēvāḷpēndra 1324 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>It seems to register a grant (details are lost) made by the king Vīra Sōyidēvāḷpēndradēva while giving audience at his court in the palace at (the capital) Barahkanyāpura (Bārakūru) and in the presence of <hi rend="italic">mahāpradāna</hi> Sōvaṇṇa <hi rend="italic">sēnabōva,</hi> Siṅgaṇa <hi rend="italic">sāhaṇi,</hi> Eraḍu-Kōlabaḷiyavaru, the <hi rend="italic">bāhattaraniyōgi,</hi> Viṭhaṇa and others. The place Rājāḍi is mentioned.</p>						

						<p>It is dated Śaka 1247, Raktākshi, Āshāḍha Śu. 7, Thursday. It corresponds to 1324 A.D., June 29, Friday.</p>						

						</summary>
